<p>Armand's peculiar diction piqued my curiosity - is it an affectation, a speech impediment, or did he give himself Krantzberg syndrome*?</p>
</blockquote>
<p>Sort of a cross between the last two. In this setting, your particular brand of doing magic directly impacts how your brain works, in often idiosyncratic ways. For example, Jude's strong reality manipulation ironically burdens him with bad executive dysfunction and makes it hard for him to sort out priorities.</p>
<p>Armand's distorted speech is a direct consequence of, and analogous to, how he chops and screws miscellaneous grimoires until they actually work. It's basically a magically-induced speech impediment.</p>

